Date: Wed,28 Aug 2002
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source: La Prensa (Nicaragua), Wed 28 Aug 2002 [Trans. & edited by Mod.JW]
<http://www.laprensa.com.ni/regionales/>

Nicaragua: First Dengue Hemorrhagic Fatality in 2002
---------------------------------------
A 9-year-old boy, resident of Ocotal, Department of Nueva Segovia, has
become the first dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF) fatality in 2002. After 3
days of illness he was hospitalized last Saturday [24 Aug 2002] night and
died 2 hours later. The Ocotal hospital sees 2-3 DHF cases a week.
The Ministry of Health reported almost 1100 cases of dengue in 2002 in the
Department of Nueva Segovia, including 377 who have attended health units.
The other townships severely affected are Jicaro, Quilali, Jalapa, & Wiwili,
according to Dr Giovanni Roa, Departmental Director of Silais in Nueva
Segovia.
--
Pablo Nart
UK
<p.nart@virgin.net>
