[6]
Date: Sat 31 Aug 2002
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source AP worldstream, Via Newsline, Fri 30Aug 2002 [edited]

Mexico: 4 Dengue Fever Deaths Reported
-----------------------------------------
On Fri 31 Aug 2002 officials confirmed 24 cases of dengue and 2 of dengue
hemorrhagic fever in Mexico state, which borders Mexico City. Health
officials were spraying mosquito breeding grounds and said the measures
appeared to be keeping the painful disease away from Mexico City, a
metropolis of 18 million. So far, the mosquito-borne fever has remained in
rural Mexico. Last week, officials in Morelos state, on the southern border
of Mexico City, confirmed 13 cases of dengue and 2 cases of dengue
hemorrhagic fever.
Federal authorities reported that dengue has killed at least 4 people in
Mexico. The deaths occurred far from Mexico City. Dengue killed 2 women in
the southeastern state of Veracruz, another woman in the southern state of
Campeche, and an elderly man in the Pacific coast state of Colima. Health
officials estimate that nearly 3005 people across Mexico have contracted
non-life-threatening dengue since January 2002. Another 424 have been
treated for the hemorrhagic form.
--
Pablo Nart
UK
<p.nart@virgin.net>
